    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Urera baccifera are anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant. The anti-inflammatory activity of Urera baccifera is attributed to the presence of flavonoids, which are bioactive compounds that have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. The antimicrobial properties of this plant are due to its content of saponins, which have been found to exhibit broad-spectrum antibacterial and antifungal activities, thereby making it effective against various infections. Urera baccifera also exhibits antioxidant properties, which are mediated by the presence of polyphenolic compounds such as ellagic acid and gallic acid, that neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Additionally, the volatile oils present in Urera baccifera have been found to possess anti-diarrheal and anti-emetic activities, making it a useful treatment for gastrointestinal disorders.",
