    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Urera baccifera are Flavonoids and Saponins which have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities. The Flavonoids present in Urera baccifera include Quercetin and Kaempferol, which exhibit potent free radical scavenging ability and inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. Saponins, particularly Ursolic acid, have been found to possess anti-inflammatory, antiviral, and antimicrobial properties, contributing to the plant's wound-healing and antiseptic activities. The plant also contains Tannins and Glycosides, which have been reported to exhibit antimicrobial and antiviral properties, respectively. These bioactive compounds are responsible for the therapeutic effects of Urera baccifera in traditional medicine, particularly in wound healing and treating various infections.",
