    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Urera baccifera are Urera tea which is made by steeping the leaves in hot water, Urera infusion which involves steeping the leaves in cold water for an extended period, Urera tincture which is made by soaking the leaves in a solvent like ethanol, Urera decoction which involves boiling the leaves in water to release their active compounds, and Urera salve which is a topical preparation made by infusing the leaves in a carrier oil to treat skin conditions such as eczema and dermatitis. Urera tea has been traditionally used to treat various ailments including fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. Urera infusion is also used to treat fever and rheumatism. Urera tincture is used to treat digestive issues and as a remedy for sore throats. The active compounds in Urera baccifera such as flavonoids and phenolic acids are responsible for its medicinal properties.",
